NextOS Mali fbdev: force fullscreen window size on every SetWindowSize.

Why:
The mali-fbdev video driver has no window manager and only one display
surface (the framebuffer itself). MALI_CreateWindow already pins
window->w/h and window->flags to the native display, but
MALI_SetWindowSize is a no-op — so when a game calls SDL_SetWindowSize()
mid-run (Heaps/Dead Cells loading saved-config from another device,
ports persisting 854x480, etc.), SDL3 stores the requested size in
window->floating.{w,h} but the EGL surface is still bound to the native
fb size. The result is a tiny game viewport drawn into a corner of a
much larger framebuffer.

Fix:
Override MALI_SetWindowSize to clamp window->w/h and floating.{w,h}
back to the native display, then synthesize an SDL_EVENT_WINDOW_RESIZED
carrying the native size. Any engine that listens to resize events
adapts; engines that just call SDL_GetWindowSize() will see the native
size on the next query.

Same logic applied at create-time: floating.{w,h} also pinned, so a
later SetWindowSize triggered by SDL3 internals (aspect-ratio passes,
etc.) cannot drift below native.

--- a/src/video/mali-fbdev/SDL_malivideo.c
+++ b/src/video/mali-fbdev/SDL_malivideo.c
@@ -383,6 +383,8 @@ bool MALI_CreateWindow(SDL_VideoDevice *_this,
     /* Janela ocupa a tela inteira — fbdev não tem gerenciador de janelas. */
     window->w = displaydata->native_display.width;
     window->h = displaydata->native_display.height;
+    window->floating.w = window->w;
+    window->floating.h = window->h;
     window->flags |= SDL_WINDOW_FULLSCREEN | SDL_WINDOW_BORDERLESS;


@@ -478,9 +480,21 @@ bool MALI_SetWindowPosition(SDL_VideoDevice *_this, SDL_Window *window)
     return true;   /* posição fixa em fbdev; sucesso silencioso */
 }

+/* NextOS: fbdev tem 1 surface = todo o display; ignorar pedidos de tamanho
+ * dos jogos (configs persistidos de outros devices etc.) e devolver sempre
+ * o tamanho nativo. Mantém window->floating.{w,h} sincronizado pra evitar
+ * que aspect-ratio passes do SDL3 voltem a "diminuir" depois. */
 void MALI_SetWindowSize(SDL_VideoDevice *_this, SDL_Window *window)
 {
-    (void)_this; (void)window;
+    SDL_DisplayData *dd = MALI_GetDisplayData();
+    if (!dd) {
+        return;
+    }
+    window->w = dd->native_display.width;
+    window->h = dd->native_display.height;
+    window->floating.w = window->w;
+    window->floating.h = window->h;
+    SDL_SendWindowEvent(window, SDL_EVENT_WINDOW_RESIZED, window->w, window->h);
 }

 void MALI_ShowWindow(SDL_VideoDevice *_this, SDL_Window *window)
